<subSubSection id="88C065359B21FFA568992B0E54A3C523" lastPageId="30" lastPageNumber="31" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C06536BE9B21FFA768992B0E565DC672" blockId="28.[189,303,265,291]" box="[189,303,265,291]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<heading id="9B2D81D29B21FFA768992B0E565DC672" bold="true" box="[189,303,265,291]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" reason="3">
<emphasis id="F2AEEAAC9B21FFA768992B0E565DC672" bold="true" box="[189,303,265,291]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C06536BE9B21FFA568992B3F5348C6DD" blockId="28.[188,1401,311,478]" lastBlockId="30.[189,1399,265,397]" lastPageId="30" lastPageNumber="31" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
We collected a damaged specimen that could only be identified to genus level as 
<taxonomicName id="07DA4D3D9B21FFA76C5F2B305270C600" authorityName="Hertz" authorityYear="1927" box="[1147,1282,311,337]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiomusaidae" genus="Ophiomusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F2AEEAAC9B21FFA76C5F2B305270C600" box="[1147,1282,311,337]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Ophiomusa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It differs from 
<taxonomicName id="07DA4D3D9B21FFA768DB2B5C5606C625" baseAuthorityName="Wyville Thomson" baseAuthorityYear="1873" box="[255,372,346,373]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiomusaidae" genus="Ophiomusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="lymani">
<emphasis id="F2AEEAAC9B21FFA768DB2B5C5666C624" box="[255,276,347,373]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">O</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F2AEEAAC9B21FFA769002B5D5606C625" box="[292,372,346,372]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">lymani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the coverage of irregular scales on the disc center, the radial shields being smaller and more triangular, large ventral disc scales connected to the oral shield entirely covering the interradial space between the genital plates and having an ventral arm plate present on up to seven arm segments from the arm base (
<figureCitation id="58E12A3B9B21FFA769862BC35542C68F" box="[418,560,452,478]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="28.[189,232,1822,1848]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,523,1801]" captionTargetId="figure-236@28.[189,1399,523,1801]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="Fig. 13. A–G. Ophiomusa lymani (Wyville Thomson, 1873) (IDSSE EEB-SW0008). A. Dorsal disc. B. Ventral disc. C. Oral frame. D. Ventral arm base. E. Dorsal arm base. F. Ventral arm. G. Lateral arm plate with arm spines. H–L. Ophiomusa sp. (IDSSE EEB-SW0010). H. Dorsal disc. I–J. Ventral disc. K. Dorsal arm. L. Ventral arm. Abbreviations: as = adoral shield; ars = arm spine; dap = dorsal arm plate; gs = genital slit; lap =lateral arm plate; os = oral shield; rs = radial shield; tp = tentacle pore; vap = ventral arm plate. Scale bars: A = 10 mm; B = 15 mm; C–E = 2 mm; F, H–L = 1 mm; G = 500 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6419559" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6419559/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 13H–L</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="07DA4D3D9B21FFA76A662BC35580C68F" box="[578,754,452,478]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiomusaidae" genus="Ophiomusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="F2AEEAAC9B21FFA76A662BC355BBC68F" box="[578,713,452,478]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Ophiomusa</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
forms a sister clade to 
<taxonomicName id="07DA4D3D9B21FFA76C252BC35307C68F" baseAuthorityName="Wyville Thomson" baseAuthorityYear="1873" box="[1025,1141,452,478]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiomusaidae" genus="Ophiomusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="lymani">
<emphasis id="F2AEEAAC9B21FFA76C252BC35364C68F" box="[1025,1046,452,478]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">O</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F2AEEAAC9B21FFA76C012BC35307C68F" box="[1061,1141,452,478]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">lymani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on our molecular tree (see below). In the phylogeny by 
<bibRefCitation id="A44B4B4F9B20FFA66A632B0E54FBC672" author="Christodoulou M. &amp; O'Hara T. D. &amp; Hugall A. F. &amp; Arbizu P. M." box="[583,905,265,291]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="3909 - 3912" refId="ref36904" refString="Christodoulou M., O'Hara T. D., Hugall A. F. &amp; Arbizu P. M. 2019. Dark ophiuroid biodiversity in a prospective abyssal mine field. Current Biology 29 (22): 3909 - 3912. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. cub. 2019.09.012" type="journal article" year="2019">
Christodoulou 
<emphasis id="F2AEEAAC9B20FFA66AD22B0D5443C672" box="[758,817,265,291]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">et al.</emphasis>
(2019)
</bibRefCitation>
, this sister clade is composed of 
<taxonomicName id="07DA4D3D9B20FFA66D2F2B0E56F6C617" authority="(Koehler, 1922 a)" baseAuthorityName="Koehler" baseAuthorityYear="1922" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiomusaidae" genus="Ophiomusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="faceta">
<emphasis id="F2AEEAAC9B20FFA66D2F2B0E5252C672" box="[1291,1312,265,291]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">O</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F2AEEAAC9B20FFA66D0B2B0E5205C672" box="[1327,1399,265,291]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">faceta</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="A44B4B4F9B20FFA668E12B2B560EC617" author="Koehler R." box="[197,380,300,326]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="1 - 480" refId="ref38296" refString="Koehler R. 1922 a. Ophiurans of the Philippine seas and adjacent waters. United States National Museum Bulletin 5 (100): 1 - 480." type="journal article" year="1922">Koehler, 1922a</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="07DA4D3D9B20FFA6699B2B2A5467C617" authority="(Koehler, 1922 a)" baseAuthorityName="Koehler" baseAuthorityYear="1922" box="[447,789,300,327]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiomusaidae" genus="Ophiomusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="facunda">
<emphasis id="F2AEEAAC9B20FFA6699B2B2A56A6C616" box="[447,468,301,327]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">O</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F2AEEAAC9B20FFA669C72B2B5530C617" box="[483,578,300,326]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">facunda</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="A44B4B4F9B20FFA66A762B2B547EC617" author="Koehler R." box="[594,780,300,326]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" pagination="1 - 480" refId="ref38296" refString="Koehler R. 1922 a. Ophiurans of the Philippine seas and adjacent waters. United States National Museum Bulletin 5 (100): 1 - 480." type="journal article" year="1922">Koehler, 1922a</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, which suggests that our specimen may also belong to one of these species. 
<taxonomicName id="07DA4D3D9B20FFA669F82B4855C6C638" baseAuthorityName="Koehler" baseAuthorityYear="1922" box="[476,692,335,361]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiomusaidae" genus="Ophiomusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="faceta">
<emphasis id="F2AEEAAC9B20FFA669F82B4855C6C638" box="[476,692,335,361]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Ophiomusa faceta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="07DA4D3D9B20FFA66B772B485371C63B" box="[851,1027,335,362]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiomusaidae" genus="Ophiomusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="F2AEEAAC9B20FFA66B772B4854A8C638" box="[851,986,335,361]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Ophiomusa</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
by having irregular disc scales on the disc center and radial shields separated by a single layer of disc scales, but differs by lacking a ventral arm plate beyond the second arm segment, smooth dorsal disc surface and 6–7 arm spines on the lateral arm plate. 
<taxonomicName id="07DA4D3D9B20FFA669AC2BBE5507C682" baseAuthorityName="Koehler" baseAuthorityYear="1922" box="[392,629,441,467]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiomusaidae" genus="Ophiomusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="facunda">
<emphasis id="F2AEEAAC9B20FFA669AC2BBE5507C682" box="[392,629,441,467]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Ophiomusa facunda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="07DA4D3D9B20FFA66B282BBE54CEC685" box="[780,956,441,468]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiomusaidae" genus="Ophiomusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="F2AEEAAC9B20FFA66B282BBE54E1C682" box="[780,915,441,467]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Ophiomusa</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
by having a rough dorsal disc surface and radial shields separated by a single layer of disc scales, but differs in having large dorsal disc scales, the entire ventral surface occupied by a large interradial scale, in lacking a ventral arm plate beyond the third arm segment and having 6–7 arm spines on the lateral arm plate. The differences between those species and our specimen prevent us from associating it with either of them.
</paragraph>
